isMultipleMarker

Returns if marker is to be repeated in this line style.

Returns:
boolean - true means several marker evenly spaced will be rendered.

setMultipleMarker

public void setMultipleMarker(boolean multi)
Sets if marker is to be repeated in this line style.

Parameters:
multi - - true means several markers will be rendered. MULTIMARKER_ALONG_PATH is set by default if current multiple marker position is not MULTIMARKER_END_POINTS or MULTIMARKER_ALL_POINTS

setMultipleMarkerPosition

public void setMultipleMarkerPosition(java.lang.String position)
Sets the multiple marker position. Values other than MULTIMARKER_NONE, means that multiple markers will be rendered (no need to call method setMultipleMarker).

Parameters:
position - valid values are: MULTIMARKER_NONE - no multiple markers MULTIMARKER_ALONG_PATH - markers will be rendered along line path, starting at marker defined position (which also defines the marker interval). MULTIMARKER_END_POINTS - markers at line end points MULTIMARKER_ALL_POINTS - markers at line points

getMultipleMarkerPosition

public java.lang.String getMultipleMarkerPosition()
Returns the multiple marker position. It has effect if multiple marker parameter of this object has been set to true.

Returns:
MULTIMARKER_ALONG_PATH or MULTIMARKER_END_POINTS or MULTIMARKER_ALL_POINTS

setCased

public void setCased(boolean cased)
Sets if line style should delay the drawing of line parts to get a better visual representation, with no overlap of lines at intersections. This is useful to render highways or roads that have intersections.

Parameters:
cased - - true to get lines without crossing at intersections.

isCased

public boolean isCased()
Returns if line style should delay the drawing of line parts to get a better visual representation, with no overlap of lines at intersections.

Returns:
boolean - true means to get lines without crossing at intersections.
